Requirements
------------

dnf-extra-tests works on Python 2.7.

Following executables and Python modules are required to run
dnf-extra-tests:

- `dnf executable <https://github.com/rpm-software-management/dnf/>`_
- `repoquery plugin
  <https://github.com/rpm-software-management/dnf-plugins-core/>`_
- `behave Python module <http://github.com/behave/behave/>`_
- `createrepo_c Python module <https://github.com/Tojaj/createrepo_c/>`_
- `dnf Python module <https://github.com/rpm-software-management/dnf/>`_


Installation
------------

Install the requirements mentioned above and copy the distribution into
any directory you like.


Support
-------

If you are having issues, please report them via the issue tracking
system. Any feedback is more than welcome.

- issue tracker: https://github.com/rholy/dnf-extra-tests/issues


Contributions
-------------

Since I am a bit demanding person and I want to avoid any unnecessary
conflicts, I don't accept any contributions. On the other hand, once
it turns out that there is a potential contributor, I'll move the
repository under https://github.com/rpm-software-management/ where the
contributions can be accepted.

- version control system: https://github.com/rholy/dnf-extra-tests